<h3>11. Satisfying videos</h3>
<p>This just might be the most universally liked and least controversial genre ever: the satisfying video. Whether it’s <a href="https://www.tiktok.com/@asmrsoap15/video/7000431524638248198?is_copy_url=1&amp;is_from_webapp=v1&amp;q=soap%20cutting&amp;t=1639386576241">soap cutting</a> or <a href="https://www.tiktok.com/@cakerepost/video/6931416822210301186?is_copy_url=1&amp;is_from_webapp=v1&amp;q=satisfying%20cake%20decorating&amp;t=1639386710346">cake icing</a> or <a href="https://www.tiktok.com/@relaxify/video/7034960685301828869?is_copy_url=1&amp;is_from_webapp=v1&amp;q=oddlysatisfying&amp;t=1639386854641">freezing bubbles</a>, there’s something super therapeutic and gratifying about this kind of content.</p>
<blockquote class="tiktok-embed" cite="https://www.tiktok.com/@pezzottipainting/video/7040583259964656902" data-video-id="7040583259964656902" style="max-width: 605px;min-width: 325px;" >
