<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/how-to-schedule-facebook-posts/">How to Schedule a Post on Facebook: A Quick and Easy Guide</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://blog.hootsuite.com">Social Media Marketing &amp; Management Dashboard</a>.</p>
";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Karin Olafson";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32127:"<p>If you’ve ever scrambled to get regular content published to your brand’s Facebook Page, you’ve probably wondered if there’s a way to schedule Facebook posts ahead of time. Well, there is!</p>
<p>When you schedule Facebook posts, managing a <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/how-to-create-a-social-media-content-calendar/">social media content calendar</a> becomes far more efficient. Scheduling posts can help your brand post consistently and stay on top of posting schedules. That way, you can avoid long gaps between posts with little effort.</p>
<p>There are two ways you can schedule posts on Facebook:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Natively. </strong>This method uses Facebook’s built-in posting scheduler.</li>
<li><strong>Using third-party schedulers.</strong> Publishing tools like Hootsuite can be used to schedule social media posts across platforms. Advanced features like bulk scheduling are available.</li>
</ul>

<div class="content-upgrade _bonusVariantContentUpgrade"><a href="https://hootsuite.com/resources/blog/social-media-content-calendar" class="cover" data-ga-track-id="ContentUpgrade_Top_CTA" target="_blank"></a><p><strong>Bonus: <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Download our free, customizable social media calendar template</span></strong> to easily plan and schedule all your content in advance.</p>
</div>
<h2>Why schedule Facebook posts?</h2>
<p>In a nutshell, scheduling Facebook posts can help your business:</p>
<ul>
<li>Save time creating individual posts</li>
<li>Post regularly</li>
<li>Connect and engage with more people</li>
<li>Increase your <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/social-media-engagement/">social media engagement</a></li>
<li>See the big picture of your posting strategy and keep all of your social accounts on brand</li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>How to schedule a post on Facebook using Facebook Business Suite</strong></h2>
<p>To schedule Facebook messages or posts, you need to have a Facebook Page.</p>
<p>(Don’t have one? Find out<a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/steps-to-create-a-facebook-business-page/"> how to create a Facebook business page</a> in just a few steps.)</p>
<p>Once your Page is set up, follow this step-by-step guide to learn how to schedule future posts.</p>
<p><strong>Step 1: Write your post</strong></p>
<p>After opening Facebook to your timeline, <strong>click Pages</strong> in the top left corner of your dashboard to navigate to your business’s Facebook Page.</p>
<p>Then, navigate to <strong>Business Suite </strong>in the menu:</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-2.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-273858" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-2.png" alt="Facebook Pages Business Suite" width="2560" height="1278" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-2.png 2560w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-2-310x155.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-2-620x310.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-2-768x383.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-2-1536x767.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-2-2048x1022.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" /></a></p>
<p>Now, click <strong>Create Post</strong>:</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-3.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-273866" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-3.png" alt="Create Post" width="2552" height="1254" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-3.png 2552w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-3-310x152.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-3-620x305.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-3-768x377.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-3-1536x755.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-3-2048x1006.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2552px) 100vw, 2552px" /></a></p>
<p>If you need inspiration, here are some tips on creating <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/perfect-facebook-post-key-ingredients/">an engaging Facebook post.</a></p>
<p><strong>Step 2: Preview the post</strong></p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-4.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-273874" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-4.png" alt="preview post" width="2560" height="1262" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-4.png 2560w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-4-310x153.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-4-620x306.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-4-768x379.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-4-1536x757.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-4-2048x1010.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" /></a></p>
<p>In the <strong>Placements</strong> section, check where you want your post to be published. You will be able to publish it to your Page and the connected Instagram account at the same time.</p>
<p>As you draft the post, you’ll be able to preview what it will look like on desktop and mobile. If anything looks off, make changes to optimize the post. Now is the time to check if link previews are pulled correctly.</p>
<p><strong>Step 3: Select a date and time</strong></p>
<p>If you don’t want to publish your post right away, click on the arrow next to the <strong>Publish</strong> button at the bottom of the page.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-5.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-273882" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-5.png" alt="select date and time" width="2544" height="1256" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-5.png 2544w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-5-310x153.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-5-620x306.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-5-768x379.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-5-1536x758.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-5-2048x1011.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2544px) 100vw, 2544px" /></a></p>
<p>Then, choose the day you want the post to be published and the time it should go live.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-6.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-273890" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-6.png" alt="choose day and time" width="2540" height="1254" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-6.png 2540w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-6-310x153.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-6-620x306.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-6-768x379.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-6-1536x758.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-6-2048x1011.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2540px) 100vw, 2540px" /></a></p>
<p>Finally, click <strong>Save</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>Step 4: Schedule your post</strong></p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-7.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-273898" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-7.png" alt="schedule post" width="2552" height="1262" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-7.png 2552w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-7-310x153.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-7-620x307.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-7-768x380.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-7-1536x760.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-7-2048x1013.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2552px) 100vw, 2552px" /></a></p>
<p>Click the blue <strong>Schedule Post</strong> button, and that’s it! Your post is now in the publishing queue. That means it’s ready to go live on the day and time you set.</p>
<h3><strong>How to edit scheduled Facebook posts in Business Suite</strong></h3>
<p>You might want to edit, delete or reschedule the Facebook posts in your queue. Here’s where you can find the queue and edit it.</p>
<ol>
<li>Navigate to <strong>Scheduled Posts</strong> in the Business Suite. There, you’ll see all of your scheduled posts.</li>
<li>Click on the post you want to edit to view the details.</li>
<li>Click on the three dots icon. You’ll see several options: Edit Post, Duplicate Post, Reschedule Post and Delete Post.</li>
<li>Make your edits and click <strong>Save</strong>. By clicking the arrow next to the Save button, you can also choose to publish the post immediately or reschedule it.</li>
</ol>
<p>It’s that easy!</p>
<h2><strong>How to schedule a post on Facebook using Hootsuite</strong></h2>
<p>Once you’ve <a href="https://help.hootsuite.com/hc/en-us/articles/1260804308069">connected your Facebook Page to your Hootsuite account</a>, this is how to schedule Facebook posts using the app.</p>
<p><strong>Step 1: Click Create Post</strong></p>
<p>Navigate to the content creation icon in the menu on the left side of the dashboard. Then, click <strong>Post</strong>.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-14.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-273954" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-14.png" alt="Hootsuite create post" width="2576" height="1236" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-14.png 2560w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-14-310x149.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-14-620x297.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-14-768x368.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-14-1536x737.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-14-2048x983.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2576px) 100vw, 2576px" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Step 2: Select the Facebook Page you want to publish to</strong></p>
<p>Check the box next to the right Facebook account.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-15.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-273962" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-15.png" alt="select Facebook page" width="2270" height="1222" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-15.png 2270w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-15-310x167.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-15-620x334.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-15-768x413.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-15-1536x827.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-15-2048x1102.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2270px) 100vw, 2270px" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Step 3: Create your post</strong></p>
<p>Write the text, add and edit your image, and add a link.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-16.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-273970" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-16.png" alt="create post with text image and link" width="2290" height="1204" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-16.png 2290w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-16-310x163.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-16-620x326.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-16-768x404.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-16-1536x808.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-16-2048x1077.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2290px) 100vw, 2290px" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Step 4: Schedule a publication time</strong></p>
<p>Tap <strong>Schedule for later</strong>. This will bring up a calendar. Choose the date and time you want the post to be published.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-17.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-273978" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-17.png" alt="schedule for later" width="2304" height="1210" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-17.png 2304w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-17-310x163.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-17-620x326.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-17-768x403.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-17-1536x807.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-17-2048x1076.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2304px) 100vw, 2304px" /></a></p>
<p>Hootsuite’s Facebook scheduling app makes it easy to post at the right times to generate high engagement.</p>
<p>The <a href="https://www.hootsuite.com/platform/analyze">Best Time to Publish</a> looks at your past engagement data to suggest optimal times to post on every network, not just Facebook!</p>
<p>(If you’d like to learn more, check out how the <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/best-time-to-post-on-facebook-twitter-instagram/#How_to_find_the_best_time_to_post_on_social_media">Best Time to Publish feature works for Hootsuite’s own social channels</a>.)</p>
<p><strong>Step 5: Click Schedule</strong></p>
<p>Your post is now scheduled to go live on Facebook and will be published at the exact time you set.</p>
<h3><strong>How to schedule multiple Facebook posts at once in Hootsuite</strong></h3>
<p>Hootsuite’s <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/how-to-bulk-schedule/">bulk schedule tool</a> makes handling a busy posting schedule more efficient. The tool lets you schedule a maximum of 350 posts at once.</p>
<p>To schedule multiple Facebook posts, save your Facebook content as a CSV file.</p>
<p>Include these details for each post:</p>
<ul>
<li>The date and time (using 24-hour time) that your post should publish.</li>
<li>The caption.</li>
<li>A URL (this is optional).</li>
</ul>
<p>Note that you can’t add emojis, images or videos to bulk posts. But you can include those afterward by editing each individual scheduled post in Hootsuite.</p>
<p>After you upload your CSV file, the Bulk Composer asks you to review all the posts. Once you’ve made your edits and uploaded any additional media files, select<strong> Schedule</strong>.</p>
<p>Don’t forget that you can edit individual posts afterward in Hootsuite’s Publisher (in the Planner and Content tab).</p>
<p>Learn more about Hootsuite’s bulk scheduling tool here:</p>
<p><iframe loading="lazy" title="How to Schedule Posts in Bulk Using Hootsuite" width="640" height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/CyrlryIfY_A?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
<h3><strong>How to auto-schedule Facebook posts in Hootsuite</strong></h3>
<p>With <a href="https://help.hootsuite.com/hc/en-us/articles/1260802320709-Automatically-schedule-a-post#autoschedule-a-post-0-0">Hootsuite’s AutoSchedule feature</a>, you can avoid gaps in your social media calendar. The tool will automatically schedule your posts for publication at optimal, high-engagement times. </p>
<p>Here’s how to use the auto-scheduling feature:</p>
<p><strong>Step 1: Compose your post </strong></p>
<p><strong>Step 2: Click Schedule for later</strong><br />
This will bring up the scheduling calendar. Instead of manually selecting when your post should go live, navigate to <strong>AutoSchedule</strong> above the calendar.</p>
<h3><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-19.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-273994" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-19.png" alt="" width="2270" height="1204" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-19.png 2270w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-19-310x164.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-19-620x329.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-19-768x407.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-19-1536x815.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-19-2048x1086.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2270px) 100vw, 2270px" /></a></h3>
<p><strong>Step 3: Turn the AutoSchedule toggle to On</strong></p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-20.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-274002" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-20.png" alt="turn AutoSchedule to on" width="2250" height="1232" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-20.png 2250w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-20-310x170.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-20-620x339.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-20-768x421.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-20-1536x841.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-20-2048x1121.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2250px) 100vw, 2250px" /></a></p>
<p>Then, click <strong>Done</strong>. AutoSchedule is enabled!</p>
<h3><strong>How to view and edit scheduled Facebook posts in Hootsuite</strong></h3>
<p><strong>Step 1: Navigate to the Publisher</strong></p>
<p>Head to the<strong> Publisher </strong>section of your dashboard (use the calendar icon in the left-hand side menu).</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-21.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-274010" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-21.png" alt="Hootsuite publisher" width="2002" height="1272" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-21.png 2002w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-21-310x197.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-21-620x394.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-21-768x488.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-21-1536x976.png 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 2002px) 100vw, 2002px" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Step 2: Go to the Planner or Content tab</strong></p>
<p>Both tabs will take you to your scheduled posts.</p>
<p>The <strong>Planner </strong>gives you a calendar view of your scheduled posts:</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-22.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-274018" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-22.png" alt="planner calendar view" width="1832" height="1260" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-22.png 1832w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-22-310x213.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-22-620x426.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-22-768x528.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-22-1536x1056.png 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 1832px) 100vw, 1832px" /></a></p>
<p>The <strong>Content </strong>shows you a list of scheduled posts. Both views work for editing and rescheduling posts — the one you choose is up to your personal preference.</p>
<p><strong>Step 3: Click on the post you want to edit</strong></p>
<p>Here’s how this looks in the <strong>Content tab</strong>:</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-23.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-274026" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-23.png" alt="content tab" width="2576" height="1262" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-23.png 2560w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-23-310x152.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-23-620x304.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-23-768x376.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-23-1536x752.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-23-2048x1003.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2576px) 100vw, 2576px" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Step 4: Edit your scheduled post</strong></p>
<p>At the bottom of the post, you have the option to either <strong>Edit</strong> or <strong>Delete</strong> your post.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-24.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-274034" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-24.png" alt="edit scheduled post" width="2572" height="1240" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-24.png 2560w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-24-310x149.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-24-620x299.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-24-768x370.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-24-1536x741.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-24-2048x987.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2572px) 100vw, 2572px" /></a></p>
<p>To open your post and make edits, click <strong>Edit</strong>. Here, you can reschedule your post or edit its contents.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-25.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-274042" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-25.png" alt="reschedule post or edit contents" width="2276" height="1198" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-25.png 2276w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-25-310x163.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-25-620x326.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-25-768x404.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-25-1536x808.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Schedule-Facebook-post-25-2048x1078.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2276px) 100vw, 2276px" /></a></p>
<p>The <strong>Delete</strong> button will erase the post from your content queue.</p>
<h2>Hootsuite vs. Facebook Business Suite</h2>
<p>If you’re looking to schedule and automatically post content to <strong>Facebook <em>and</em> Instagram, Twitter, LinkedIn, YouTube and Pinterest</strong>, Hootsuite is a great choice. It&#8217;s easy to use, and it comes with many useful collaboration features for teams. You can also use Hootsuite for social media analytics, social listening, and answering all of your comments and DMs from one place.</p>
