<h2>Instagram scheduling tools</h2>
<h3>1. Hootsuite’s Composer</h3>
<p>Create Instagram posts on the fly or schedule them for later by using Hootsuite’s Composer. With an easy-to-use interface, the Composer is a powerful publisher that comes packed with features that will help you get the most out of your Instagram posts, including editing, customizing, and, of course, scheduling.</p>
<p>Plus, use the <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/best-time-to-post-on-facebook-twitter-instagram/">Best time to Publish recommendations</a>, which are based on your unique historical posting data, to make sure you schedule your posts for the times when you are likely to get the most engagement, click-throughs, or impressions.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Instagram-Tools-1.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-302181" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Instagram-Tools-1-620x359.png" alt="Hootsuite Composer bread n coffee post" width="620" height="359" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Instagram-Tools-1-620x359.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Instagram-Tools-1-310x179.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Instagram-Tools-1-768x444.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Instagram-Tools-1-1536x889.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Instagram-Tools-1-2048x1185.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /></a><br />
Source: Hootsuite</p>
<p><a class="hs-btn hs-btn-green" href="http://hootsuite.com/plans">Try Hootsuite for free</a></p>
<h3>2. Hootsuite’s bulk scheduler</h3>
<p>Save time and resources by using <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/how-to-bulk-schedule/">Hootsuite’s bulk scheduling tool</a>. Bulk scheduling your Instagram posts allows you to streamline your social media campaigns, giving you an opportunity to focus on other areas of your business. Hootsuite’s bulk scheduler means you can post up to 350 posts ahead of time across various channels, not just Instagram.</p>
<h2>Instagram analytics tools</h2>
<h3>3. Instagram Insights</h3>
<p>Creator and business accounts have access to Instagram business tools like <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/instagram-analytics-tools-business/">Insights</a>. From the Insights tab, you can learn about who’s following you, when they’re most active, and what type of content is most popular. Some data disappears after 7-14 days, so consider the following tools for more detailed reporting.</p>
<h3><a href="https://hootsuite.com/platform/analyze">4. Hootsuite Analytics</a></h3>
<p>Hootsuite offers features that go above and beyond Instagram’s analytics tool. From the Hootsuite dashboard, you dig deeper into data from the past and run customizable or historical reports whenever the need arises. You can also monitor your account’s response time and rank Instagram comments by positive or negative sentiment.</p>
<p><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Instagram-Tools-2.png"><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-302189" src="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Instagram-Tools-2-620x312.png" alt="Hootsuite Analytics Instagram overview" width="620" height="312" srcset="https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Instagram-Tools-2-620x312.png 620w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Instagram-Tools-2-310x156.png 310w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Instagram-Tools-2-768x387.png 768w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Instagram-Tools-2-1536x774.png 1536w, https://blog.hootsuite.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Instagram-Tools-2-2048x1032.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /></a></p>
<p>Hootsuite Analytics is available to <a href="https://www.hootsuite.com/plans">Pro and Team plans</a>.</p>
